      "content": "it just feels like there's no way to un-fail. every time i try to think of a way to fix the debt or rebuild, the weight of it just crushes me. like, even if i fix the money, the damage to my reputation and how my family sees me is permanent. at this point, it feels less like a setback and more like a total ending. i just want the noise and the shame to stop.",
